NOTICE

This model wraps IgBert, a paired/unpaired antibody language model developed by
Henry Kenlay, Frederic A. Dreyer, Bruno Sherborne, and Charlotte M. Deane at
Exscientia.

Model weights: https://huggingface.co/Exscientia/IgBert
Paper: "Large scale paired antibody language models" (arXiv:2403.17889, 2024)

The IgBert weights are asserted under the MIT License per the HuggingFace model
card (`Exscientia/IgBert`, which declares `license: mit`). A separate Zenodo
deposit of the same weights (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.10876909) lists CC-BY-4.0.
Since Exscientia is the rights-holder for both releases, we rely on the more
permissive MIT license and provide attribution to the paper and both releases
to satisfy either license.
